On December 10, 2020, President Donald Trump issued an executive order regarding the order of succession within the Department of Defense. The order outlines the officials who would act as the Secretary of Defense in the event that the Secretary is unable to perform their duties. The order lists the officials in a specific order, with the Deputy Secretary of Defense being the first in line to act as Secretary. The order also includes exceptions, stating that individuals serving in an acting capacity or who do not meet the requirements for serving as Secretary cannot act as Secretary. The executive order revokes a previous executive order from 2010 regarding the order of succession in the Department of Defense. The order concludes with a general provision stating that it does not create any enforceable rights or benefits.